In GC, the combination with flame ionization detection or mass spectrometry, is widely used to determine the sugar composition of an EPS [36]. The GC–MS spectrum of EPS from Exiguobacterium sp. VK2 showed the existence of d-galactose, d-glucose, mannose, xylose, that belonging to the retention times of 16.05, 18.32, 19.2 and 20.47 (Fig. 2
                           ). The gluco-galactan property of EPS indicated that it is a heteropolymer as per earlier report [37,38]. Hence, the collected spectrum was matched with the data available in the NIST database. (Table 1
                           ).
